ColdFusion 10 has deprecated the attribute key for the tag cfcache. The corresponding new attribute is region. However key is still supported to ensure backward compatibility Also, the CFCACHE tag has a changed behavior in ColdFusion9. If CFCACHE tag is used without end tag then instead of caching only current page, now it will be caching the whole request.
  • VALUE,METADATA,STRIPWHITESPACE,THROWONERROR,ID,KEY,USECACHE,IDLETIME,DEPENDSON,NAME are new attributes added.
  • DIRECTORY, CACHEDIRECTORY, PORT, PROTOCOL attributes are deprecated in ColdFusion9.

Check the usage of attribute key and region of tag cfcache. Also
		 there are changes for CFCACHE tag in ColdFusion9. To cache only a page fragement use the tag with end tag.
		 
 
Check the usage for the new attributes VALUE,METADATA,STRIPWHITESPACE,THROWONERROR,ID,KEY,USECACHE,IDLETIME,DEPENDSON,NAME for tag cfcache. 
Note now the directory is specified at ehcache.xml.
